To find the height of a binary search tree (BST), you can implement a recursive function that calculates the height by finding the maximum height between the left and right subtrees. Here's how you can do it:

```cpp
int findHeight(Node* root) {
    if (root == nullptr) {
        return -1; // Height of an empty tree is -1
    }

    int leftHeight = findHeight(root->left);
    int rightHeight = findHeight(root->right);

    // Return the maximum height between left and right subtrees, plus 1 for the current node
    return max(leftHeight, rightHeight) + 1;
}
```

